abstract: Former Ohio Gov. Ted Strickland has endorsed Joe Biden for president, promising important support from the state's industrial working class regions while highlighting some of the former vice president's potential challenges in the state.
snippet: Former Ohio Gov. Ted Strickland has endorsed Joe Biden for president, promising important support from the state's industrial working class regions while highlighting some of the former vice president's potential challenges in the state.
lead_paragraph: COLUMBUS, Ohio — Former Ohio Gov. Ted Strickland has endorsed Joe Biden for president, promising important support from the state's industrial working class regions while highlighting some of the former vice president's potential challenges in the state.
headline_main: Former Ohio Gov. Ted Strickland Endorses Biden for President
headline_print_headline: Former Ohio Gov. Ted Strickland Endorses Biden for President

abstract: An associate of U.S. President Donald Trump's personal lawyer Rudy Giuliani is expected to appear in court on Tuesday, as federal prosecutors seek to have him jailed for allegedly concealing a $1 million payment they said he received from Russia before his arrest.
snippet: An associate of U.S. President Donald Trump's personal lawyer Rudy Giuliani is expected to appear in court on Tuesday, as federal prosecutors seek to have him jailed for allegedly concealing a $1 million payment they said he received from Russia b...
lead_paragraph: NEW YORK — An associate of U.S. President Donald Trump's personal lawyer Rudy Giuliani is expected to appear in court on Tuesday, as federal prosecutors seek to have him jailed for allegedly concealing a $1 million payment they said he received from Russia before his arrest.
headline_main: Giuliani Associate Due in Court as Prosecutors Seek to Revoke Bail
headline_print_headline: Giuliani Associate Due in Court as Prosecutors Seek to Revoke Bail

abstract: On the eve of his expected impeachment in the U.S. House of Representatives, President Donald Trump accused Democrats of pursuing an "illegal, partisan attempted coup" and declaring war on American democracy as they seek to remove him from office for pressing Ukraine to investigate political rival Joe Biden.
snippet: On the eve of his expected impeachment in the U.S. House of Representatives, President Donald Trump accused Democrats of pursuing an "illegal, partisan attempted coup" and declaring war on American democracy as they seek to remove him from office ...
lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — On the eve of his expected impeachment in the U.S. House of Representatives, President Donald Trump accused Democrats of pursuing an "illegal, partisan attempted coup" and declaring war on American democracy as they seek to remove him from office for pressing Ukraine to investigate political rival Joe Biden.
headline_main: On Eve of Expected Impeachment, Trump Lashes Out at Pelosi, Democrats
headline_print_headline: On Eve of Expected Impeachment, Trump Lashes Out at Pelosi, Democrats

abstract: A small group of President Donald Trump's fiercest conservative critics, including the husband of the president's own chief adviser, is launching a super PAC designed to fight Trump's reelection and punish congressional Republicans deemed his “enablers."

lead_paragraph: NEW YORK — A small group of President Donald Trump's fiercest conservative critics, including the husband of the president's own chief adviser, is launching a super PAC designed to fight Trump's reelection and punish congressional Republicans deemed his “enablers."
headline_main: Trump Conservative Critics Launch PAC to Fight Reelection

abstract: The president and his enablers have replaced conservatism with an empty faith led by a bogus prophet.
snippet: The president and his enablers have replaced conservatism with an empty faith led by a bogus prophet.
lead_paragraph: Patriotism and the survival of our nation in the face of the crimes, corruption and corrosive nature of Donald Trump are a higher calling than mere politics. As Americans, we must stem the damage he and his followers are doing to the rule of law, the Constitution and the American character.

abstract: The great drama of the Russia investigation has turned out to be a dark Coen brothers farce.
snippet: The great drama of the Russia investigation has turned out to be a dark Coen brothers farce.
lead_paragraph: An essential motion picture for the Trump era is one that I didn’t particularly care for when it first came out. I speak, of course, of “Burn After Reading,” the Coen brothers’ pitch-black comedy about morons attempting spycraft in Washington, D.C., which upon first viewing seemed too unremittingly misanthropic, too grimly contemptuous of its characters, without the flashes of grace that illuminate the darkness in most Coen depictions of human folly.

abstract: The last election weakened our democracy. Why aren’t we preparing for the next one?
snippet: The last election weakened our democracy. Why aren’t we preparing for the next one?
lead_paragraph: American democracy has a target on its back: Disinformation has become a firm fixture of political campaigns in the digital age. Given the country’s polarized politics and history of close elections, the prospect that sophisticated influence operations, foreign and domestic, could shape the outcome of the 2020 presidential race is very real — and despite the searing experience of 2016, America is not ready.

abstract: U.S. Defence Secretary Mark Esper said on Monday that he needed to speak with his Turkish counterpart to understand how serious President Tayyip Erdogan was when he said he could shut down the Incirlik air base, which hosts U.S. nuclear warheads.
snippet: U.S. Defence Secretary Mark Esper said on Monday that he needed to speak with his Turkish counterpart to understand how serious President Tayyip Erdogan was when he said he could shut down the Incirlik air base, which hosts U.S. nuclear warheads.
lead_paragraph: ABOARD A U.S. MILITARY AIRCRAFT — U.S. Defence Secretary Mark Esper said on Monday that he needed to speak with his Turkish counterpart to understand how serious President Tayyip Erdogan was when he said he could shut down the Incirlik air base, which hosts U.S. nuclear warheads.
headline_main: Pentagon Chief: Need to Speak With Turkish Counterpart to Understand Erdogan Base Comments
headline_print_headline: Pentagon Chief: Need to Speak With Turkish Counterpart to Understand Erdogan Base Comments

abstract: Cafeteria workers at the debate site enlisted the candidates’ support as they fought successfully for a better contract. The candidates had said they would not cross a picket line to participate.
snippet: Cafeteria workers at the debate site enlisted the candidates’ support as they fought successfully for a better contract. The candidates had said they would not cross a picket line to participate.
lead_paragraph: LOS ANGELES — The next Democratic presidential debate will go on as scheduled Thursday, after negotiators on Tuesday reached agreement in a labor dispute that had threatened to upend the event while highlighting organized labor’s influence with the leading Democratic presidential candidates.
